2022 market szn is officially over! Thank you for the kind words and support throughout the years 🥹💗 2022 brought so many new challenges - a tougher economy, changes to the algorithm, a return to in-person events (to name a few!) Things haven't been easy but I feel like I'm finally growing into myself. Tbh, in 2020 and 2021, space queen grew at a much faster rate than I could keep up with. It took me forever to find a decent balance between work/life, but I think I'm finally here. Thank you for supporting this shy girls' dreams, you've literally changed my life just by tagging along on my journey.

2022 was a big year for personal growth. I started the year with big hopes for growing my business in ways I just wasn't mentally prepared for - I wanted to hire an assistant and produce so much more work and collections. Thinking back, I was dreaming big but not really taking the right steps to get there. I definitely wasn't in the right headspace to lead a team or expand my business because I was doing such a poor job of taking care of myself. It took a lot of work (and I'm still learning) but I think I'm finally at a good place with my work routine as a full-time artist, and I'm getting a lot better about my diet and exercise which has been hugely transformative. I can actually get through most work days without getting sleepy and sad. I thought I'd be more sad about not reaching the business goals I had in mind for 2022, but taking the year to center my mental/physical health has been a huge win - and now it feels like there's finally more space for creativity and experimentation in my life. Happy new year friends 💗 hoping that 2023 brings you everything you need #cuteplanters #kawaii #kawaiiartist #fulltimeartist #smallbusiness #ceramics #concreteart #magicalgirl #dreamy #dreamyart

Faerie pets collection sneak peak!! This is a WIP of some of the neopets pieces that will be releasing this month 💝 #neopets #neopetsart #faeriebrush #faerieneopets #faeriecore #faeriecoreaesthetic #y2knostalgia #valentinescollection

I really love these neopets pieces they've brought me so much joy making them 🥹 I always feel a lil funny at the end of collection launches because while I feel so relieved to be done with it, I can't help but feel like there's so much more that I want/wish I could add. Like maybe if I just did it like that it couldve been 100000% better and reached a trillion more people 😆 which honestly, is really unhealthy thinking. I think sometimes I just have to feel good about where I'm at. If this was the best of my ability at that specific time - that's okay 👌 it kind of makes every piece of work feel more like a time capsule of my thoughts and skills at the time. Which is also kinda cooler? Lol idk. Just wanted to share some thoughts
.
.

Last week I had had the pleasure of taking @1loma & @merida_yyy 's Nerikomi and Neriage workshop at the @centredartrozynski . It was a 3-day intensive workshop and probably one of the best learning experiences I've ever had. If you ever get the opportunity to take a Marina and Merida workshop, I HIGHLY recommend you take the chance. I drove 7hrs to get there, and I can honestly say it was worth it lol. 

Here's a carafe, cup, and bowl collection I made during the workshop. These are still unfired, so they'll be even more vibrant once they're finished. I can't wait to make more nerikomi work in the future! 
.
